  "source": "rag_hpo_paper",
  "full_text": "We report two families in which propositi had severe bilateral sensorineural hearing loss, a preauricular pit or tag, and duplication of the ureters or bifid renal pelvices. Other relatives had one or more of these anomalies in a pattern suggesting autosomal dominant inheritance with reduced penetrance and variable expressivity. We suggest the term \"branchio-oto-ureteral syndrome\" to designate this condition.",
